				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd say you should draw the full name table. Just because most TV's will not show those lines this is no reason to leave crap there.  If, during a game, you don't want to write anything there in order to save time, at least clear them at the start and never touch those tiles again. At least you will be sure they are blank.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Writing $00 to the screen is good to do at your reset routine, because if someone does a soft reset while playing your game, you'll most likely want to have a clear screen before you do anything to it.</div>
<br />Personal opinion: I never clear blocks of memory, I'd rather write clean code that does not assume values in RAM that was not initialized. And I initialize EVERYTHING before using. In a complex program, it's hard to be sure what was in the name tables before, so you'd better clear it all when redrawing it, and not risk displaying crap by accident.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
